why has my cat starting eating mice my beloved year old cat has always brought mice home to the door usually in a played with state but just lately there is very little left of them he seems to leave the tail and inners he eats very well and has food available whenever why has he started this uck errin b of course i am not watching my cat do this he goes out most nights when the weather is good i cannot sit up all night just in case he brings a mouse home because he can because its fun to him and because he's the hunter of the house it's his job after all and he's bringing them in to show you because he loves you and wants you to be proud of him i had a cat who was an absolute scream the first time he bought home a dead headless mouse i praised him too much and told him he was such a good boy what did the silly sod do went out a bought home an old crisp packet of course i praised him again he thought this was the best game ever and he duly went back out and bought home a dirty used drinking straw this went on for hours and by o'clock that evening my waste paper basket was full up ha ha ha they are funny don't tell him off for it he's just having fun although the mice aint laughing much and he's enjoying bringing you some presents he won't always eat them he'll just bite the heads off and bring you the body just dont let him kiss you ha ha ha The Shining (film) Garfield Spidey Super Stories Squidward Tentacles Cat RuneScape quests The Jazz Singer Care Bears EastEnders Ron and Fez Mickey Mouse Customs and etiquette of Japan I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Tom and Jerry (MGM) Sinfest Social rule Rod Stewart Trailer Park Boys Bart Sells His Soul Jennifer Lopez Pitaten The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe House Mouse Friends Little Britain The Catcher in the Rye Humphrey Bogart The Amber Spyglass John the Baptist One Piece minor characters Late Night with Conan O'Brien Scream (film) Silent Night, Deadly Night AFI 100 Years series Joke Similaritie